                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13703973" author="ekoifman" created="Tue, 9 Jul 2013 23:11:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1. added logic in hcat/webhcat scripts to come up with defaults that make sense in the standard build tree for HIVE_HOME, HCAT_PREFIX and TEMPLETON_HOME (unless defined by user)&lt;br/&gt;
2. propagate the same values through Ant build files so that TestWebHCatE2e can run w/o having to define HCAT_PREFIX, HIVE_HOME explicitly.&lt;br/&gt;
3. improved a few error messages&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13705044" author="thejas" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 20:43:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should we warn the user that the HIVE_HOME is being set to {$bin}/../.. , as hive home is not defined ?&lt;br/&gt;
In an installation, it would be confusing to see errors saying that lib directory was not found under HIVE_HOME, when the hive home was not specified by the user, or based on hive in the PATH.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13705087" author="ekoifman" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 21:28:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure this is possible as the user will not see this output unless you return non-0 status code, at least in case of WebHCat.  And if you print a message with exit status=0, then it may interfere with &apos;normal&apos; output sent to WebHCat.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="13705115" author="thejas" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 21:41:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, webhcat users would not see this message. But I think it will be useful for somebody using hcat cli directly or trying to debug a webhcat installation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13710033" author="ekoifman" created="Tue, 16 Jul 2013 18:18:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hive4820.2.patch includes changes per Thejas&apos; comments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
